  "text": "Real-time processing is very important for speech recognition applications. Another issue to be addressed is the computational efficiency of the 3-D Viterbi method. Its computation amount is ( is the number of directions) times as large as that of the standard Viterbi search. The reduction might be achieved by introducing another implementation of the transition probability between directions, applying various pruning techniques according to the talker movement and using a stack decoding approach [CITATION_1] . The development of the real-time signal processing system is currently proceeded by members of our research group.",
